Prague FFA Chapter
August 31 at 1:18 PM ·

Prague FFA Chapter just received the National 3 Star Award!

The National Chapter Award Program is designed to recognize FFA chapters that actively implement the mission and strategies of the organization. These chapters improve chapter operations using the National Quality Chapter Standards (NQCS) and a Program of Activities (POA) that emphasize growing leaders, building communities and strengthening agriculture. Chapters are rewarded for providing educational experiences for the entire membership.

post_text: This year the theme at Prague Schools is “Be Extraordinary,” based on the book The Fred Factor by Mark Sanborn. This year we will be recognizing staff and students who exhibit the “Fred Way,” those who do exceptional and remarkable work. If you have not read the book, we encourage each and every person to read it and challenge yourself to be a Fred. Fred was a postman that delivered exceptional service to his customers. Virtual parents, send us a photo or give us a shout out when you see your child do something extraordinary, we would love to hear about it and it will give them the opportunity to earn a Fred award and be recognized on our social media platforms. Those can be sent to vfeltman@prague.k12.ok.us

post_text: Tomorrow is the day! We are so excited to see our students either face to face or virtually! A few reminders: 1) Students will need to sit with their own family members on the bus. 2) Temperatures will be taken at all schools. There is no drop-off at the Underground. 3) The new Early Childhood Center is open (we have a few things to finish) but are happy we will be able to let students start in their new building. 4)Students in grades PK-1 can be dropped off in front of the new school, students grades 2-5 can be dropped off at the upper elementary. Parents can bring them in. 5)Please drop middle school students off on the South side of the planter. The bus lane is on the North side of the planter. Staff will be on hand to help students with lockers and supplies. We ask that middle school parents only come in to enroll students. 6) Virtual students will need to log on and begin their assignments starting tomorrow. If you have any questions please contact us at 405-567-2281 and we will be happy to help you. See you tomorrow!

GEAR UP students selected for National Youth Leadership Summit

Brooke Stanley and Ben Foster, both incoming Sophomore students, were chosen to attend the GEAR UP National Youth Leadership Summit in Washington D.C. in July. Brooke and Ben were among 8 students that were selected out of 1,000 Seminole State College GEAR UP students. Unfortunately, COVID-19 cancelled the conference this year. So proud of all they do and accomplish for Prague School and SSC GEAR UP!

post_text: Prague Schools will host 2 graduation celebrations. 1) Will be May 8. The seniors will start in the Middle School parking lot at 6:45 and drive through town for a small parade and then go back to the High School parking lot where seniors will be called up 4 at a time to be recognized. The parking lot will hold approximately 130 cars, 85 of those are reserved for the seniors, administrators, and Board members. This will be live streamed via Facebook. This allows students with military commitments after May to still participate. Everyone must stay in their vehicles because the State Department has closed all schools until at least June and no gatherings over 10 are allowed. 2) On July 17 at 7pm we will host a traditional ceremony in the New Gym pending no CDC or State/Local restrictions.

post_text:
ATTENTION:

TONIGHT, Friday April 10th at 8:20 pm (20:20) we will be honoring our Senior class of 2020. We will turn on the lights at the football field for 20 minutes. Please, remember to maintain social distancing protocols and stay in your vehicle!

High schools across the nation will light up their football fields on Friday, April 10 at 8:20 p.m. for the nationwide "Be the Light" Campaign.

The campaign was designed to recognize and honor all of the 2020 seniors and their academic and extra-curricular accomplishments.

The lights on the football field will be on for 20 minutes and 20 seconds, and residents are encouraged to drive by and honk in support for this graduating class of seniors, while still practicing social distancing. PLEASE DO NOT STOP, GATHER, OR PARK CARS. Just drive by and honk if you would like to. This is not an event or an invitation to gather, it is a symbol of hope and support. #bethelight #reddevilstrong

post_text: The Prague Middle School Leadership Team and Student Council volunteered at the Oklahoma Regional Food Bank in OKC. The students packaged foods that will be sent to food pantries in churches or schools throughout Oklahoma. These students worked diligently for 2.5 hours and packaged agrand total weight of 4,198 pounds of food product, which equates to 3,497 meals.

post_text: The Middle School Gifted and Talented students were treated to a day at the National Cowboy & Western Heritage Museum in OKC and a wondeful lunch by Debra and Gary Kinslow. The students enjoyed it all very much! We had a guided tour through the museum, experiencing Native American handy work and art, along with other forms of western history and art. The student favorite was getting to hang out in and experience an old western town. A HUGE THANK YOU to Debra and Gary Kinslow.

The Thursday Parent Teacher Conferences will be made up on Tuesday the 18th from 4pm to 7pm.
